    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Missing Ingredient Of the Pyrameter</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>John Chervokas letter on May 7 article introducing poetic form known as pyrameter; editor's note: sample of readers' pyrameters will appear on May 28 (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Thanks for introducing the pyrameter last Sunday [''A Poetic Challenge: Nine Lines, 45 Syllables''], but you omitted one critical piece of information. The fifth line of a pyrameter is the theme and/or title of the verse.</p>
        <p>JOHN CHERVOKAS  Ossining</p>
        <p>Editor's Note: A sample of readers' pyrameters will appear on May 28.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
